            "content_html": "<img src=\"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1365071?u=a28e0813dc14227725639ff1d19a94f36319e285&v=4\" width=\"64\" height=\"64\" alt=\"\"/><br/>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Description</h3>\n\n<ul dir=\"auto\">\n<li>Change /docs/ links to /en-US/docs/</li>\n<li>Add missing <code class=\"notranslate\">{{WebExtAPIRef</code> in declarativenetrequest/index.md</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Motivation</h3>\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">There is a missing <code class=\"notranslate\">{{WebExtAPIRef</code> in the DNR article. I might have overlooked it before because the bot was spitting out tons of \"useless\" warnings about non-resolvable URLs. I fixed it by replacing <code class=\"notranslate\">/docs/</code> with <code class=\"notranslate\">/en-US/docs/</code>, and then <code class=\"notranslate\">/en-US/en-US/docs/</code> with <code class=\"notranslate\">/en-US/docs/</code>.</p>\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Additional details</h3>\n\n<h3 dir=\"auto\">Related issues and pull requests</h3>\n\n\n\n<p dir=\"auto\">This is a follow-up to <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load title\" data-id=\"1710946766\" data-permission-text=\"Title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/mdn/content/issues/26793\" data-hovercard-type=\"pull_request\" data-hovercard-url=\"/mdn/content/pull/26793/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/mdn/content/pull/26793\">#26793</a></p>\n",
